{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-index-js","path":"/thursday-sociology/","result":{"data":{"site":{"meta":{"title":"Ansin","description":"Ansin's portfolio","url":"https://imyentsen.github.io","author":"Ansinlau","twitter":"Ansinlau","adsense":""}},"post":{"id":"cf5a8141-b19d-5359-81f2-a5bfab072776","html":"<p>Imagine that you are an administrative coordinator of a university department, and you have to design the posters of your weekly guest lecture series. The recurring task could make a disturbing experience, given you don’t have any design background nor your colleagues do. </p>\n<p>Your budget is tight. Most of the money should be spent on the speaking fee of the speakers. It’s technically impossible to hire a professional designer to do the job every week with a reasonable payment. </p>\n<hr>\n\n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-bottom: 1.0725rem; max-width: 1800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\">\n      <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"info architecture\" title src=\"/static/12e96ac25b209276cae18525591bbd3d/d9c39/info_arch.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/12e96ac25b209276cae18525591bbd3d/41099/info_arch.jpg 500w,\n/static/12e96ac25b209276cae18525591bbd3d/a2510/info_arch.jpg 1000w,\n/static/12e96ac25b209276cae18525591bbd3d/d9c39/info_arch.jpg 1800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n<figcaption>The types of data input of the generator</figcaption>\n<hr>\n<p>The situation happens to the administrative coordinators of the Department of Sociology at National Taiwan University. They need to mitigate the hurdle on the design side. However, they still want to deliver a consistent and decent visual identity for the lecture series.</p>\n<hr>\n\n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-bottom: 1.0725rem; max-width: 1801px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\">\n      <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"a glance at the website\" title src=\"/static/7bffe85ed07536ed55d1a5da0d2786cf/91094/website.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/7bffe85ed07536ed55d1a5da0d2786cf/41099/website.jpg 500w,\n/static/7bffe85ed07536ed55d1a5da0d2786cf/a2510/website.jpg 1000w,\n/static/7bffe85ed07536ed55d1a5da0d2786cf/91094/website.jpg 1801w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1801px) 100vw, 1801px\">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n<figcaption>A glance at the website</figcaption>\n<hr>\n<p>I designed and developed a website for the department to automize the process. It started with several times of interviews to reach a consensus on how to standardize the information on the posters, such as speech title, name of the speaker, description of speech, etc. The information was then turned into the inputs of a form. Then, based on the inputs agreed, I created a questionnaire-like website on which they can generate posters automatically by completing the form. </p>\n<p>The user interface of the website mitigates the training costs. The inputs are organized in comprehensive order. There is almost no learning curve if the users have had any experience in filling online forms provided by Google, Survey Cakes, Typeform, etc. Anyone at the department can easily use it, and it only takes 1 minute to complete the form. Once the user has filled in the form and clicked the “generate” button on the page, a pop-up window shows up and allows them to download the poster. </p>\n<hr>\n\n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-bottom: 1.0725rem; max-width: 1800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\">\n      <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"The posters generated\" title src=\"/static/0aea7fe9e3741925a62dc70c7eba52ba/d9c39/3posters.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/0aea7fe9e3741925a62dc70c7eba52ba/41099/3posters.jpg 500w,\n/static/0aea7fe9e3741925a62dc70c7eba52ba/a2510/3posters.jpg 1000w,\n/static/0aea7fe9e3741925a62dc70c7eba52ba/d9c39/3posters.jpg 1800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n<figcaption>A closer look at some posters generated</figcaption>\n<hr>\n<p>The design utilizes the images taken at the department and the schools by myself. I took the double exposure picture with the conventional in-camera way. One exposure was taken at the classroom during a speech at the Department of Sociology, while the other was taken at the centre of the university where some famous traditional architectural characteristics such as “sudare tiles” can be found. </p>\n<hr>\n\n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-bottom: 1.0725rem; max-width: 1800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\">\n      <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"The posters generated\" title src=\"/static/4d1fe65399369160c9872ace7e66456e/d9c39/cover.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/4d1fe65399369160c9872ace7e66456e/41099/cover.jpg 500w,\n/static/4d1fe65399369160c9872ace7e66456e/a2510/cover.jpg 1000w,\n/static/4d1fe65399369160c9872ace7e66456e/d9c39/cover.jpg 1800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n<figcaption>The main image on the poster</figcaption>\n<hr>\n<p>The double exposure picture displays a long roadway extending forwardly from a university building to the end of the centre of the picture. It overlaps with the exposure of in-door lecture, which implies that the content of the lectures penetrates from the in-class field to the broader societies outside.</p>\n<p>The generator randomly gives the poster a primary colour from a pre-defined colour palette. It distinguishes the posters of every different speech generated. While they are assembled all together, it’s easy to recognize them as one single lecture series given its consistent look.</p>\n<hr>\n\n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-bottom: 1.0725rem; max-width: 1800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\">\n      <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"It&#x2019;s easy to recognize them as one single lecture series given its consistent look.\" title src=\"/static/74ba7266c4d695a5fb56b402740cee9d/d9c39/asm.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/74ba7266c4d695a5fb56b402740cee9d/41099/asm.jpg 500w,\n/static/74ba7266c4d695a5fb56b402740cee9d/a2510/asm.jpg 1000w,\n/static/74ba7266c4d695a5fb56b402740cee9d/d9c39/asm.jpg 1800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n<figcaption>It&#x2019;s easy to recognize them as one single lecture series given its consistent look.</figcaption>\n<hr>","frontmatter":{"layout":"post","title":"Poster Generator of Thursday Sociology","path":"/thursday-sociology/","category":["Branding","UI","UX","Frontend"],"skill":null,"role":["UX (interview)","UI","Branding","Front-end Devlopment (HTML, CSS, React)"],"description":"Poster generator website for a weekly lecture series in Sociology at National Taiwan University","date":"2019","image":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","width":500,"height":375,"src":"/static/4d1fe65399369160c9872ace7e66456e/0f3a1/cover.jpg","srcSet":"/static/4d1fe65399369160c9872ace7e66456e/0f3a1/cover.jpg 1x,\n/static/4d1fe65399369160c9872ace7e66456e/f9913/cover.jpg 1.5x,\n/static/4d1fe65399369160c9872ace7e66456e/a7715/cover.jpg 2x","srcWebp":"/static/4d1fe65399369160c9872ace7e66456e/e9589/cover.webp","srcSetWebp":"/static/4d1fe65399369160c9872ace7e66456e/e9589/cover.webp 1x,\n/static/4d1fe65399369160c9872ace7e66456e/e557c/cover.webp 1.5x,\n/static/4d1fe65399369160c9872ace7e66456e/e30b5/cover.webp 2x"},"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.3333333333333333,"src":"/static/4d1fe65399369160c9872ace7e66456e/a1eb1/cover.jpg","srcSet":"/static/4d1fe65399369160c9872ace7e66456e/4fa6c/cover.jpg 200w,\n/static/4d1fe65399369160c9872ace7e66456e/64b17/cover.jpg 400w,\n/static/4d1fe65399369160c9872ace7e66456e/a1eb1/cover.jpg 800w,\n/static/4d1fe65399369160c9872ace7e66456e/a6c62/cover.jpg 1200w,\n/static/4d1fe65399369160c9872ace7e66456e/70ff9/cover.jpg 1600w,\n/static/4d1fe65399369160c9872ace7e66456e/8d3de/cover.jpg 1800w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}